        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 4:17PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Piqua, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Springfield, Troy, Sidney, Piqua, Bellefontaine, Urbana, Tipp City,
West Milton, Northridge, Covington, St. Paris, West Liberty, Russells
Point, De Graff, Pleasant Hill, Hardin, Quincy, Russia,
Christiansburg, and North Hampton.

This includes I-75 in Ohio between mile markers 70 and 97.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
